# My collection of git hooks and commands

Some are just plain git command, some are script, found in `commands/`

### Install

`curl -L https://raw.githubusercontent.com/haoadoreorange/git-helpers/main/install.sh | sh`

### hooks

`commit-msg`: hook from [git-good-commit](https://github.com/tommarshall/git-good-commit).

### commands

##### Changing quickly between different git signatures

`commands/git-sigc.sh`

Define a `~/.gitprofile` file.

```ini
[default]
    name="Foo Baz"
    email="foo@mail.com"

[school]
    name="Foo Baz"
    email="foo@school.com"
```

then run `git sigc [--global] <profile>` (local by default) or
`git sigc [--global] <name> <email> <profile>` to configure and save/update the profile in
`~/.gitprofile` at the same time.

##### Rewrite author signature in history to the current config. DANGER: rewrite git history, replace all `Sign-off-by` matching your old username

`commands/git-sign-history.sh <old name>`

##### Remove remote tags

`git push origin --delete $(git tag -l)`. Pushing once should be faster than multiple times

##### Remove local tags

`git tag -d $(git tag -l)`

##### Remove remote branches with prefix

`git branch -a | grep branch-prefix | sed 's|remotes/origin/||' | xargs git push -d origin`

##### Split existing repository into submodules

```sh
# split the "main repo"
git subtree split -P path -b <branch>

# add new remote
git remote add submodule <url>

# push the submodule
git push -u submodule <branch>:master

# remove path
git rm -r path

# commit changes
git add -A
git commit -m 'Replace <path> with submodule'

# add the submodule
git submodule add <url> <path>

# commit the .gitmodules file
```

##### Remove files in history. DANGER: rewrite git history

`git filter-repo --invert-paths --path-glob 'dir/*.json' --force`

`--force` required if there is remote, safety measure
